+# Codex Writer Findings — CartView
+Chain: cartview-260415-092055-289b
+
+## Findings
+1. [P0] `statusBuckets` still groups by legacy `o.status` only — In [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:427), the drawer decides `served` vs `in_progress` from `o.status`, while terminal completion now comes from `Order.stage_id -> OrderStages.internal_code`. A waiter/SOM move to the `finish` stage can therefore leave the order in `В работе`, which matches the bug described in Fix 1. `getOrderStatus` in [useTableSession.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/useTableSession.jsx:797) also still returns only `{ icon, label, color }`, so CartView has no stage code to consume. FIX: extend `getOrderStatus(order)` to return `internal_code`, then make `statusBuckets` stage-first with legacy `o.status` fallback exactly as described in Fix 1.
+2. [P1] CartView still renders a single mixed flow instead of `Мои / Стол` tabs — The current file has no `Tabs` import or usage at all, and the “table orders” block is still a standalone collapsible card at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:776) with the table total in a separate card at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:873). That means Fix 2 is not present: own cart/orders and table-level orders are still mixed in one scroll, and there is no `Мои` tab with the guest bill plus a switchable `Счёт стола` summary. FIX: import shadcn `Tabs`, wrap the current “my” content and the table-orders block into exactly two `TabsContent` sections, and move the table-total presentation into the tabbed layout instead of leaving it as a global card below both sections.
+3. [P2] The planned Fix 3 condition is too narrow to satisfy its own verification — `showTableOrdersSection` is currently derived from `otherGuestIdsFromOrders.length > 0` at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:478) and [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:501), but `otherGuestIdsFromOrders` comes only from `sessionOrders`. If a second guest joins the table and has not submitted any orders yet, the task’s verification says tabs should appear, but this condition remains false and the tabs would stay hidden. FIX: separate “has other guest in the session” from “has other guest orders”; drive tab visibility from guest/session presence, and keep the table tab content/empty state based on whether other guest orders actually exist.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 3 findings (1 P0, 1 P1, 1 P2, 0 P3)
+
+## Prompt Clarity
+- Overall clarity: 3
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 2 says to keep the “current block” with the guest-only bill in the `Мои` tab, but the current `CartView.jsx` no longer has an explicit guest-bill block to reuse; only the header total and the separate global `Счёт стола` card are present. Fix 3 references `showTableOrdersSection` as the tab gate, but that variable is order-driven, not guest-driven, so it conflicts with the stated verification “second guest joins -> tabs appear”.
+- Missing context (what info would have helped): The task context says `CartView.jsx` should be about 1194 lines, but the current file is 1087 lines. A confirmed up-to-date source snapshot or exact RELEASE baseline would have removed uncertainty about whether the prompt was written against an older file shape.
+- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): Fix 4 is explicitly deferred, so I treated it as backlog-only and did not convert its missing `openReason` plumbing into a separate code finding. The prompt also says to update `BUGS.md`, but the same task marks `BUGS.md` as read-only, so I treated it as out of scope for this review-only pass.
